          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-12-11 13:05:53" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>wood as a substance</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>wood</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>A number of languages make a clear distinction between wood as a substance used in artifacts and constructions and wood used for heating or cooking. A further distinction may be made between durable wood (not readily subject to rot or to the effects of termites and borers) and less durable and therefore relatively unsatisfactory wood.</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
